(2,$t$1.2A$t$,$r$171_180$r$,$d$medium$d$,$s$How many dots are shown?$s$,$v$<svg viewBox="0 0 620 220" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><image href="/grade1-math-50-preview-assets/figure-02.svg" x="0" y="0" width="620" height="220" preserveAspectRatio="xMinYMin meet"/></svg>$v$,$e$One full ten-frame is 10. The second frame has 4 dots. 10 + 4 = 14.$e$,$n$Original Grade 1 math preview seed: TestingMom reference batch 1$n$,$c$[{"label":"A","body":"12","is_correct":false,"sort_order":1,"misconception":"Counted items but did not connect the count to the total.","misconception_tag":"cardinality_count_to_total"},{"label":"B","body":"13","is_correct":false,"sort_order":2,"misconception":"Counted items but did not connect the count to the total.","misconception_tag":"cardinality_count_to_total"},{"label":"C","body":"14","is_correct":true,"sort_order":3,"misconception":null,"misconception_tag":null},{"label":"D","body":"15","is_correct":false,"sort_order":4,"misconception":"Counted items but did not connect the count to the total.","misconception_tag":"cardinality_count_to_total"}]$c$::jsonb),
